# MUI Table Headers

When using MUI `<Table>` with `<TableHead>`, the header row must not turn grey on hover.

**Do:** Add `sx={{ "&:hover": { backgroundColor: "transparent" } }}` to the `<TableRow>` inside `<TableHead>`.

```jsx
<TableHead>
  <TableRow sx={{ "&:hover": { backgroundColor: "transparent" } }}>
    <TableCell>Column 1</TableCell>
    ...
  </TableRow>
</TableHead>
```

If the header has a custom background (e.g. gradient), keep the same hover override so the background does not change on hover:

```jsx
<TableRow sx={{ background: "...", "&:hover": { backgroundColor: "transparent" } }}>
```
